briefdescription.para: Enable the remapping of PD0 and PD1. When the HSE oscillator is not used (application running on internal 8 MHz RC) PD0 and PD1 can be mapped on OSC_IN and OSC_OUT. This is available only on 36, 48 and 64 pins packages (PD0 and PD1 are available on 100-pin and 144-pin packages, no need for remapping).

simplesect.para: ENABLE: PD0 remapped on OSC_IN, PD1 remapped on OSC_OUT.

briefdescription.para: Disable the remapping of PD0 and PD1. When the HSE oscillator is not used (application running on internal 8 MHz RC) PD0 and PD1 can be mapped on OSC_IN and OSC_OUT. This is available only on 36, 48 and 64 pins packages (PD0 and PD1 are available on 100-pin and 144-pin packages, no need for remapping).

simplesect.para: DISABLE: No remapping of PD0 and PD1

memberdef.name: AFIO_REMAP_ENABLE
memberdef.initializer: do{ uint32_t tmpreg = AFIO->MAPR; \ tmpreg |= AFIO_MAPR_SWJ_CFG; \ tmpreg |= REMAP_PIN; \ AFIO->MAPR = tmpreg; \ }while(0u)

memberdef.name: AFIO_REMAP_DISABLE
memberdef.initializer: do{ uint32_t tmpreg = AFIO->MAPR; \ tmpreg |= AFIO_MAPR_SWJ_CFG; \ tmpreg &= ~REMAP_PIN; \ AFIO->MAPR = tmpreg; \ }while(0u)

memberdef.name: AFIO_REMAP_PARTIAL
memberdef.initializer: do{ uint32_t tmpreg = AFIO->MAPR; \ tmpreg &= ~REMAP_PIN_MASK; \ tmpreg |= AFIO_MAPR_SWJ_CFG; \ tmpreg |= REMAP_PIN; \ AFIO->MAPR = tmpreg; \ }while(0u)

memberdef.name: AFIO_DBGAFR_CONFIG
memberdef.initializer: do{ uint32_t tmpreg = AFIO->MAPR; \ tmpreg &= ~AFIO_MAPR_SWJ_CFG_Msk; \ tmpreg |= DBGAFR_SWJCFG; \ AFIO->MAPR = tmpreg; \ }while(0u)
